Quiz Application
A Java console-based multiple-choice quiz that tests knowledge in programming fundamentals, web development, databases, and data structures.

What This Program Does
Presents 12 multiple-choice questions across 4 categories

Tracks user score in real-time

Validates user input to ensure proper answers (A, B, C, D)

Displays final score with performance summary

Uses Object-Oriented Programming principles with a Question class

Categories Covered
Programming Fundamentals (3 questions)

Web Development (4 questions)

Database (2 questions)

Data Structures (3 questions)

How to Run
Make sure you have Java installed on your system

Open the project in NetBeans, IntelliJ, or any Java IDE

Run the QuizApplication.java file

Follow the on-screen instructions to answer questions

